      "SummaryText": "D SUBSTANCES\n\n\n\nThe ExxonMobil Beaumont Polyethylene Plant is a world-scale producer of low density, linear low density, and high density polyethylene resins manufactured on three (3) BASFA tubular reactors and three (3) Unipol gas-phase reactors.\n\n\n\nThe facility occupies 300 acres near the Beaumont Municipal Airport. It has 240 acres of developed area for office, manufacturing and warehouse storage. \n\n\n\nThe manufacturing processes at BPEP utilize EPA RMP regulated substances including Butene, Ethylene, Hydrogen, isoPentane, and Propylene.\n\n\n\n\n\nGENERAL ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM AND CHEMICAL-SPECIFIC PREVENTION STEPS\n\n\n\nBPEP has developed programs to comply with industry's most stringent environmental, health and safety standards including the Chemical Manufacturers Association's Responsible Care program, OSHA's PSM standard and the EPA's Risk Management Plan.\n\n\n\nAdditionally, BPEP is certified as an OSHA STAR Work Site for complying with the health and safety standards set by OSHA. BPEP has been an OSHA STAR worksite since 1984.  Facilities in the STAR program are required to demonstrate exemplary safety performance and agree to work cooperatively with OSHA to serve as an example for the rest of industry to follow.  OSHA STAR participants are audited by OSHA for compliance every few years.  BPEP has earned the prestigious STAR recognition and has maintained it through nine OSHA inspections over a thirty year period.\n\n\n\nBPEP takes a systematic, proactive approach to prevent accidental releases of hazardous chemicals.  Our process safety management systems address each of the essential features of successful accident prevention programs including:\n\n\n\n-Process safety information           -Process hazard analysis              -Compliance audits\n\n-Operating procedures              -Incident investigation\n\n-Training                             -Employee participation\n\n-Mechanical Integrity                 -Hot work permit\n\n-Management of change                 -Con"
